How do I even begin? Yesterday was my Birthday, and my beautiful wife @rocka_themechanic tells me she has an evening of surprise fun. I had no idea what was in store for me…

We started at Spicy Moon for Vegan Szechuan food (my favorite!) then to a natural wine bar for an incredible glass of wine, then…we walk into the back room at Beauty Bar, and it’s filled with so many of my friends!!! 

A surprise party for me!!! I immediately burst into tears of happiness and I instantly felt bathed in love! Never have I ever thought I would have a surprise party…it was the best! 

The whole night was filled with so much love! I am so grateful to all the people in my life, and I couldn’t think of a better way to usher in the next year. I was having so much fun that these are the only photos I got of the night! Thank you to everyone who came out, there’s too many to mention. I love you all!

And special thanks to my wife, for organizing the best Birthday EVER! 

#supriseparty #birthday #fourtiesareawesome #love

Headliner Spotlight: Peekaboo Pointe is an interdisciplinary performance artist, video artist, stripper, burlesque performer and choreographer. She began performing burlesque in nightclubs in 2003 and has created a body of work that can co-exist in both traditional performance spaces and the world of nightlife entertainment. She received an MFA in Performance and Interactive Media Art and a BFA in Dance. She has been listed on 21st Century Burlesque’s Top 50 Most Influential Burlesque performers list for five years, has won seven Golden Pasties, and has had the honor of performing at The Burlesque Hall of Fame nine times. 

As a headliner she toured Australia, Canada, South Africa and across the US. Peekaboo self produced multiple international 6 week tours across Europe, and has even performed in China and Russia. She was a guest artist in Vive le Cabaret at the Edinburgh Fringe Festival, and joined the long running French Cabaret show Cabaret New Burlesque for 3 months. She was a cast member in the long running New York City shows: This is Burlesque with Murray Hill (2007-9) which ran 4 shows a week; and Guilty Pleasures (2006-7) and toured with Lucha Vavoom. Currently, she is a resident performer at The Slipper Room (2003-present), Bathtub Gin, and the legendary Duane Park (2008-present). 

Outside of Burlesque she choreographed and performed for Taylor Mac’s 24 Decades of Popular Music, and was a dancer for Gesel Mason Performance Projects piece Antithesis. She is currently creating interdisciplinary performance in NYC, and has presented work at HERE Arts, Dixon Place and Wild Project. Her video work has been presented at the Jean Cocteau Cinema and the NMSU Art Museum. 

See Peekaboo at Spellbound Burlesque presents Temptation! Tickets on sale NOW! 
https://www.spellboundburlesque.com/tickets

Wow…wow…wow. Italy, what an adventure! I’m honestly still coming down from the high of my last week! 

I started out with a couple days off in Milan. It was my first time there and it definitely won’t be my last. I loved everything about this city! Even though one of the biggest travel hiccups of my touring career happened here when @klm lost my luggage for 6 FULL days…what better place to shop for replacement clothes than Milan! As a lover of life, and a roll with the punches girl, I definitely didn’t let lost luggage get me down. I still had one full costume in my carry on bag, so the show can go on! 

@theblueeyedbombshell met me in Milan and we hopped on a train to Sequals for some rest and relaxation by the pool in the mountains, sipping Prosecco! Lots of Prosecco…🤣 

Finally, we made it to @nastyboyssaloon for @nasty_burlesque_festival_  I was so excited to finally be headlining this festival!! It’s been a long time since I’ve had this much fun!!!! Maybe it was the tequila, or maybe the place is simply a magical wonderland for wild people! Probably both. After my last set performing I jumped offstage, took another shot of tequila and got tattooed by @luiginopizza 

Around 7pm the night I left, my baggage arrived just in time to bring it home to New York, where my gorgeous wife @rocka_themechanic and our dog Squiggy were anxiously waiting at the airport. 

I love touring so much! And I’ll be planning another one in the fall…so watch out! 

#seducingtheworld #love #tattoo #nastyboys #ilovemyjob #wildchild #italy #treviso #lostluggage #travelingshowgirl

Did you know that I offer private coaching? Are you working on a new act and wanting to take your performance work to a new place? I am currently taking new students for private coaching! 

I have coached performers of all types, not just in burlesque! I have worked with performance artists, comedians, dancers, theater performers, and humans who just want to feel better in their skin and find their source of joy. 

I believe that it’s important to have support during the creative process, and for that I am always willing to work within your budget. 

Feel free to DM me with any questions or if you’d like to set up a session! #coach #seducingtheworld #artistsneedartists #buildcommunity #ilovemyjob

BIG ANNOUNCEMENT!!! 

In September of 2003, I took my top off onstage for the first time in a dive bar in Brooklyn, and my life has never been the same since. I found my passion, my love and my family, and TWENTY YEARS LATER I’m still f*#$ing doing it!!! I can’t believe so much time has passed and it just feels like yesterday that this ride started. 

So, I hope that you will join me to celebrate two decades of skripping! I’ve put together a night of performances from some of my favorite performers. There will definitely be surprise guests, a lot of mayhem, and possibly a naked pie fight! You never know!

It has taken me weeks to come down from my 20th Anniversary Celebration at @slipperroomny 

I can’t even begin to express how glad I was that on a whim, drinking rose topless on the beach with my wife @rocka_themechanic , I decided to produce a celebration show. 

The whole night was magical! I feel so honored and privileged to have the gift of 20 years in an industry that is, in all honesty, a pretty hard one to stay in. I love burlesque, the industry and mostly the community. I feel so lucky for the time that I have had, and for all the people that this crazy world has put in my path. Really, my favorite people in the world are $tr*ppers!They are the BEST! 

Every performer in the show that night held a special place in my history and in my life and I’m so glad I got to share it with all of you!! 

Here’s to 20 more years! I’m not going anywhere!!!!

Ok…Slovenia, where do I begin? It all started last year when I met @linaakif after a performance of my piece, Yes Please, she asked for an interview for a magazine, and after I spurted out…”maybe I should come to Slovenia” I didn’t expect that a year later that would actually happen. Im so grateful for everyone who came together to make it happen! @emanat_institute @mladinsko @zavod.maska thank you to the Small Arts Platform for having me as a guest artist, and again to Lina for moderating the artist talk that I was very nervous about! 

Also a huge thank you to @tatovipodob for having my as a guest in your show. I mean WOW, what an incredible group of performers!! I am blown away by the work that you are doing, and can’t WAIT to work together again!  And a note to anyone reading this, if you get a chance to see them perform DO IT! 

Thank you also to the students that came for my 2 day act development workshop. I’m looking forward to seeing the performance videos in the future!!! @s_hinoka 

#love #travelingshowgirl #seducingtheworld #myjobisrad #smallartsplatform #slovenia

Wow wow wow…Italy! (This is only part 1) 

From the beautiful spa in Rimske Toplice, Slovenia I got onto a bus through the mountains into Milan. Ten hours later I was greeted by my beautiful hostess Sera, her 2 cute cats and a big plate of pasta! The next day we drove to Switzerland, for a show @osteriateatrounione the show was so fun in a big historical theater! 

The next day, I jumped on the train to @nastyboyssaloon where I performed with the gorgeous @mizongarde and stayed up til all hours of the night drinking tequila! 

The next morning I was up and back on the train to Vincenza to teach a workshop with @hurlyburly_show 

Had drinks with the students after, and back on the train I went to Como, where I slept, woke up and taught my eye contact workshop. 

The schedule was insane, but I had such a good time. Thank you to all the students who participated in my classes and to my hosts along the way! Big thanks to @misssophiechampagne @kitty_thecactus 

#seducingtheworld #ilovemyjob #trainlife #tourlife #tour #artist #performer

Milan! Quickly becoming one of my favorite cities in Europe, and this trip really clinched it. After teaching a super $lutty class @therougeacademy @ellabottomrouge and I scored 3rd row at @rupaulsdragracelive where I got to see @vanessavanjie live and my mind was officially blown! Then of course, we had to go to the after party! 

I feel so grateful to have had a couple days to get to spend with Ella! One of my favorite parts of traveling is getting to know like minded performers all over the world, and discovering new friends. It’s absolutely the best part of touring. It makes all the sleepless nights, long bus rides, carrying luggage over cobble stones, and being homesick worth it. 

Next stop Glasgow!! 

#seducingtheworld #tour #tourlife #rupaulsdragrace #milan #rougeacademy #love #ilovemyjob

Last Wednesday I had the absolute pleasure of performing at @tansyburlesque Carrot Machine for the 2nd time! While my first act need’s never see the stage lights again, it felt really great to bring something a little different than I usually do in the burlesque world. I woke up sad, and just went with it and created something I really enjoyed performing. 

Thank you Tansy, for creating a space for curiosity and exploration to be forced onto the stage! Carrot Machine is brilliant. #carrotmachine @slipperroomny #love #performer #artist #itsart #ilovemyjob
